SKILL|llm-wiki|"Karpathy's LLM Wiki: build/query interlinked markdown KB."
STEP|1|Division of labor:** The human curates sources and directs analysis. The agent
STEP|2|Asks to create, build, or start a wiki or knowledge base
STEP|3|Asks to ingest, add, or process a source into their wiki
STEP|4|Asks a question and an existing wiki is present at the configured path
STEP|5|Asks to lint, audit, or health-check their wiki
STEP|6|References their wiki, knowledge base, or "notes" in a research context
STEP|7|Location:** Set via `WIKI_PATH` environment variable (e.g. in `~/.hermes/.env`).
STEP|8|Layer 1 — Raw Sources:** Immutable. The agent reads but never modifies these.
STEP|9|Layer 2 — The Wiki:** Agent-owned markdown files. Created, updated, and
STEP|10|Layer 3 — The Schema:** `SCHEMA.md` defines structure, conventions, and tag taxonomy.
STEP|11|Creating duplicate pages for entities that already exist
STEP|12|Missing cross-references to existing content
STEP|13|Contradicting the schema's conventions
STEP|14|Repeating work already logged
STEP|15|Determine the wiki path (from `$WIKI_PATH` env var, or ask the user; default `~/wiki`)
STEP|16|Create the directory structure above
STEP|17|Ask the user what domain the wiki covers — be specific
STEP|18|Write `SCHEMA.md` customized to the domain (see template below)
STEP|19|Write initial `index.md` with sectioned header
STEP|20|Write initial `log.md` with creation entry
STEP|21|Confirm the wiki is ready and suggest first sources to ingest
STEP|22|File names: lowercase, hyphens, no spaces (e.g., `transformer-architecture.md`)
STEP|23|Every wiki page starts with YAML frontmatter (see below)
STEP|24|Use `[[wikilinks]]` to link between pages (minimum 2 outbound links per page)
STEP|25|When updating a page, always bump the `updated` date
STEP|26|Every new page must be added to `index.md` under the correct section
STEP|27|Every action must be appended to `log.md`
STEP|28|**Provenance markers:** On pages that synthesize 3+ sources, append `^[raw/articles/source-file.md]`
STEP|29|Models: model, architecture, benchmark, training
STEP|30|People/Orgs: person, company, lab, open-source
STEP|31|Techniques: optimization, fine-tuning, inference, alignment, data
STEP|32|Meta: comparison, timeline, controversy, prediction
STEP|33|**Create a page** when an entity/concept appears in 2+ sources OR is central to one source
STEP|34|**Add to existing page** when a source mentions something already covered
STEP|35|**DON'T create a page** for passing mentions, minor details, or things outside the domain
STEP|36|**Split a page** when it exceeds ~200 lines — break into sub-topics with cross-links
STEP|37|**Archive a page** when its content is fully superseded — move to `_archive/`, remove from index
STEP|38|Overview / what it is
STEP|39|Key facts and dates
STEP|40|Relationships to other entities ([[wikilinks]])
STEP|41|Source references
STEP|42|Definition / explanation
STEP|43|Current state of knowledge
STEP|44|Open questions or debates
STEP|45|Related concepts ([[wikilinks]])
STEP|46|What is being compared and why
STEP|47|Dimensions of comparison (table format preferred)
STEP|48|Verdict or synthesis
STEP|49|Sources
STEP|50|Check the dates — newer sources generally supersede older ones
STEP|51|If genuinely contradictory, note both positions with dates and sources
STEP|52|Mark the contradiction in frontmatter: `contradictions: [page-name]`
STEP|53|Flag for user review in the lint report
STEP|54|Scaling rule:** When any section exceeds 50 entries, split it into sub-sections
STEP|55|Domain: [domain]
STEP|56|Structure created with SCHEMA.md, index.md, log.md
STEP|57|Read all sources first
STEP|58|Identify all entities and concepts across all sources
STEP|59|Check existing pages for all of them (one search pass, not N)
STEP|60|Create/update pages in one pass (avoids redundant updates)
STEP|61|Update index.md once at the end
STEP|62|Write a single log entry covering the batch
STEP|63|Create `_archive/` directory if it doesn't exist
STEP|64|Move the page to `_archive/` with its original path (e.g., `_archive/entities/old-page.md`)
STEP|65|Remove from `index.md`
STEP|66|Update any pages that linked to it — replace wikilink with plain text + "(archived)"
STEP|67|Log the archive action
STEP|68|`[[wikilinks]]` render as clickable links
STEP|69|Graph View visualizes the knowledge network
STEP|70|YAML frontmatter powers Dataview queries
STEP|71|The `raw/assets/` folder holds images referenced via `![[image.png]]`
STEP|72|Set Obsidian's attachment folder to `raw/assets/`
STEP|73|Enable "Wikilinks" in Obsidian settings (usually on by default)
STEP|74|Install Dataview plugin for queries like `TABLE tags FROM "entities" WHERE contains(tags, "company")`
STEP|75|Setup:**
STEP|76|Continuous background sync via systemd:**
STEP|77|**Never modify files in `raw/`** — sources are immutable. Corrections go in wiki pages.
STEP|78|**Always orient first** — read SCHEMA + index + recent log before any operation in a new session.
STEP|79|**Always update index.md and log.md** — skipping this makes the wiki degrade. These are the
STEP|80|**Don't create pages for passing mentions** — follow the Page Thresholds in SCHEMA.md. A name
STEP|81|**Don't create pages without cross-references** — isolated pages are invisible. Every page must
STEP|82|**Frontmatter is required** — it enables search, filtering, and staleness detection.
STEP|83|**Tags must come from the taxonomy** — freeform tags decay into noise. Add new tags to SCHEMA.md
STEP|84|**Keep pages scannable** — a wiki page should be readable in 30 seconds. Split pages over
STEP|85|**Ask before mass-updating** — if an ingest would touch 10+ existing pages, confirm
STEP|86|**Rotate the log** — when log.md exceeds 500 entries, rename it `log-YYYY.md` and start fresh.
STEP|87|**Handle contradictions explicitly** — don't silently overwrite. Note both claims with dates,
